name: Cucumber
description: Cucumbers are cylindrical green fruits with edible seeds surrounded by a crisp, watery flesh. They are low in calories and a good source of hydration.

name: Carrot
description: Carrots are root vegetables known for their vibrant orange color and sweet, crunchy taste. They are rich in beta-carotene, fiber, vitamins, and minerals.

name: Broccoli
description: Broccoli is a green vegetable with tightly clustered florets on edible stems. It is high in fiber, vitamins C and K, and contains various antioxidants.

name: Tomato
description: Tomatoes are red, juicy fruits commonly used as vegetables in cooking. They are rich in lycopene, vitamin C, potassium, and other nutrients.

name: Spinach
description: Spinach is a leafy green vegetable packed with nutrients like iron, vitamins A and K, and antioxidants. It has a mild, slightly sweet flavor.

name: Bell Pepper
description: Bell peppers come in various colors like red, green, and yellow. They are crunchy and sweet with a mild flavor. Bell peppers are rich in vitamins and antioxidants.
